 <i>lux</i> ‘light’. The girl's name is common in Italy and elsewhere, and is found as a learned, Latinate doublet of   Lucy   in England.  St Lucia  of Syracuse, who was martyred in  304 , was a very popular saint in the Middle Ages; she is often represented in medieval art as blinded and with her eyes on a platter, but the tradition that she had her eyes put out is probably based on nothing more than the association between light and eyes."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":30,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":39,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Lucia Peverell was born in 1185, in Sampford Peverell, Devon, England. She had at least 1 son with Alain Basset. She died in 1238, in Cornwall, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 53."},"et":{"Cir 1185–1238":"1185–1238","1208–1262":"1208–1262","1230–Male":"1230–Surnud","1185–1238":"1185–1238","1238":"1238","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1230":"1230","1185":"1185","1262":"1262","Cir 1185":"1185","1208":"1208","Sampford-Peverell, Devon, England":"Sampford Peverell, Devon, England","Teludy, Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Devonshire, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"Cir 1185–1238":"1185–1238","1208–1262":"1208–1262","1230–Male":"1230–Kuollut","1185–1238":"1185–1238",